  "texts": [
    "Consequently, if producers have better information than consumers about product risk, strict liability provides better incentives for the activity level than a negligence rule (Landes & Posner, 1985, 550).",
    "However, the consumer is not incentivised to reduce their product use under a strict product liability regime.",
    "The producer would fully cover any losses the consumer incurs (Shavell, 2004, 215).",
    "This is different under a negligence rule, which induces the socially optimal activity level by the consumer.",
    "When choosing between a strict liability or negligence standard, a critical consideration is identifying which party, the producer or the consumer, has a greater capacity to prevent accidents through their level of activity."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}